President Biden and First Lady Jill Biden welcomed guests to the White House for a dinner on the occasion of the second USA-Africa Summit. The theme for the holiday decorations at the White House this year was "We the People," which symbolizes the deep connection between Africa and the United States. President Biden acknowledged the history of slavery and the contributions of the African diaspora in building the country. He expressed optimism about the shared future of both continents, particularly with the involvement of young people. President Sall of Senegal thanked President Biden for the invitation and expressed a desire to advance the partnership between Africa and the United States in an inclusive manner. The dinner was attended by African leaders, Vice President Kamala Harris, and Second Gentleman Douglas Emhoff.